                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/><supplied reason="lost">r</supplied>egem qua redacta in pot<supplied reason="lost">estatem <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> Caesaris</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Augusti populique Romani senatu<supplied reason="lost">s Dis Immortalibus</supplied> <lb n="3"/>supplicationes binas ob res prosp<supplied reason="lost">ere ab eo gestas et</supplied> <lb n="4"/>ipsi ornamenta triumph<supplied reason="lost">alia decrevit</supplied> <lb n="5"/>pro <expan><abbr>consul</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> Asiam provinciam op<supplied reason="lost">tinuit <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>atus</ex></expan> pro <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aetore</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="6"/>divi Augusti iterum Syriam et Ph<supplied reason="lost">oenicen optinuit</supplied> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Nach G. Alfödy ist der &amp;quot;&amp;quot;Titulus Tiburtinus&amp;quot;&amp;quot; am ehesten P. Sulpicius Quirinus zuzuweisen, der 21 n. Chr. starb (Tac., Ann. 3, 48).</p>
